    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in the bag to avoid mess. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped cucumber</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(save the rest for later!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>in a bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>smashed sesame cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
